

 You need both to run Python in VS Code:

Extension = Helper in the editor
Interpreter = Engine that runs your code

Python Extension (VS Code) : Adds Python support to VS Code. Installed via Extensions tab in VS Code
Python Interpreter (System): Actually runs Python code.  Installed via Terminal or python.org

*VS Code Python extension like a translator â€” it helps VS Code understand.The Python Extension in VS Code: adds features to VS Code, like:

Syntax highlighting
Code suggestions
Debugging tools
Jupyter notebook support

* Interpreter is the real Python engine that runs your .py files


